@* ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
   File: Components/Pages/Dashboard.razor

   PURPOSE: Post-login landing page. Shows the current user's
   name and which roles they belong to. This page requires
   authentication — unauthenticated users are redirected to login.

   KEY CONCEPTS:
   • @page "/dashboard"  →  Maps this component to the URL /dashboard
   • @attribute [Authorize]  →  Requires login; redirects if not authenticated
   • [CascadingParameter] HttpContext  →  Gives access to the current user
   ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ *@

@page "/dashboard"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using PuppetFestAPP.Web.Data
@attribute [Authorize]


@* ── Page title appears in the browser tab ── *@
<PageTitle>Dashboard - Puppet Fest Merch</PageTitle>


@* ── Greeting: shows the logged-in user's email/username ── *@
<h1>Hello, @context.User.Identity?.Name!</h1>

<p>Welcome to the Puppet Festival Merchandise Management System.</p>

@* ── Role display: iterates all defined roles and shows which
     ones the current user belongs to ── *@
<div class="card mt-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">Your Roles</h5>
        <ul>

            @foreach (var role in AppRoles.AllRoles)
            {
                @if (context.User.IsInRole(role))
                {
                    <li><strong>@role</strong></li>
                }
            }

        </ul>
    </div>

<pagetitle>Dashboard - Puppet Fest Merch</pagetitle>
<div class="container" class="mt-4">
<h1>Hello, @UserName!</h1>
<p class="text-muted">Welcome to the Puppet Festival Merchandise Management System.</p>
<!-- Stats Summary Row -->
<div class="row" class="mt-4">
<div class="class="col-md-4"">
<div class="card border-primary shadow-sm h-100">
<div class="card-body text-center">
<h6 class="text-uppercase text-muted">Today's Revenue</h6>
<h2 class="display-6">@TotalRevenue.ToString("C")</h2>
<small class="text-success"><i class="bi bi-cart-check"></i> From recorded sales</small>
</div></div></div></div></div>
<div class="class="col-md-4"">
<div class="card border-warning shadow-sm h-100">
<div class="card-body text-center">
<h6 class="text-uppercase text-muted">Inventory Shrinkage</h6>
<h2 class="display-6 text-danger">@ShrinkageCount</h2>
<small class="text-muted">Extra items sold via manual count</small>
</div></div></div>
<div class="class="col-md-4"">
<div class="card border-info shadow-sm h-100">
<div class="card-body text-center">
<h6 class="text-uppercase text-muted">Active Roles</h6>
<div class="mt-2">
                        @foreach (var role in UserRoles)
                        {
                            <span class="badge bg-info text-dark me-1">@role</span>
                        }
                    </div></div></div></div>
<!-- Simple Over/Under Visualizer -->
<div class="card mt-4 shadow-sm">
<div class="card-header bg-white">
<h5 class="mb-0">Manual vs. System Sales (Today)</h5>
</div>
<div class="card-body">
            @if (TotalUnitsSold > 0)
            {
                <div class="progress" style="height: 30px;">
                    @{
                        var systemPct = (double)SystemSoldUnits / TotalUnitsSold * 100;
                        var manualPct = (double)ShrinkageCount / TotalUnitsSold * 100;
                    }
                    <div class="progress-bar bg-primary" role="progressbar" style="width: @systemPct%" title="System Recorded">System: @SystemSoldUnits</div>
<div class="progress-bar bg-warning text-dark" role="progressbar" style="width: @manualPct%" title="Manual Adjustments">Manual: @ShrinkageCount</div>
</div>
<div class="mt-2 small text-muted">
<i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> Blue represents button-clicks. Yellow represents discrepancies found during reconciliation.
                </div>
            }
            else
            {
                <p class="text-center text-muted my-3">No sales activity recorded today yet.</p>
            }
        </div>

</div>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.False" Style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4">Hello, @UserName!</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Secondary" Class="mb-4">Welcome to the Puppet Festival Merchandise Management System.</MudText>

    <MudGrid GutterSize="3">
        <MudItem xs="12" md="4">
            <MudPaper Elevation="1" Class="pa-4 text-center">
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Color="Color.Secondary">Today's Revenue</MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" Class="mt-2">@TotalRevenue.ToString("C")</MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Success"><MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.ShoppingCart" /> From recorded sales</MudText>
            </MudPaper>
        </MudItem>
        <MudItem xs="12" md="4">
            <MudPaper Elevation="1" Class="pa-4 text-center">
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Color="Color.Secondary">Inventory Shrinkage</MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" Color="Color.Error" Class="mt-2">@ShrinkageCount</MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Secondary">Extra items sold via manual count</MudText>
            </MudPaper>
        </MudItem>
        <MudItem xs="12" md="4">
            <MudPaper Elevation="1" Class="pa-4 text-center">
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Color="Color.Secondary">Active Roles</MudText>
                <MudStack Direction="Row" Wrap="Wrap.Wrap" Justify="Justify.Center" Class="mt-2">
                    @foreach (var role in UserRoles)
                    {
                        <MudChip Color="Color.Info" Variant="Variant.Filled" Style="margin:0.25rem;">@role</MudChip>
                    }
                </MudStack>
            </MudPaper>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>

    <MudPaper Elevation="1" Class="pa-4 mt-4">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Manual vs. System Sales (Today)</MudText>

        @if (TotalUnitsSold > 0)
        {
            var systemPct = TotalUnitsSold == 0 ? 0 : (double)SystemSoldUnits / TotalUnitsSold * 100;
            var manualPct = TotalUnitsSold == 0 ? 0 : (double)ShrinkageCount / TotalUnitsSold * 100;
            <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-3">System Sales: @SystemSoldUnits</MudText>
            <MudProgressLinear Value="@systemPct" Color="Color.Primary" Class="mt-2" BufferValue="100" />
            <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-3">Manual Adjustments: @ShrinkageCount</MudText>
            <MudProgressLinear Value="@manualPct" Color="Color.Warning" Class="mt-2" BufferValue="100" />
            <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Color="Color.Secondary" Class="mt-3">Blue represents system-recorded sales. Yellow represents reconciliation discrepancies.</MudText>
        }
        else
        {
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Secondary" Class="mt-3">No sales activity recorded today yet.</MudText>
        }
    </MudPaper>
</MudContainer>



@code {

    // ── HttpContext cascading parameter ──
    // In Blazor, a "cascading parameter" is a value passed down from a
    // parent component (in this case, the App/Router). HttpContext contains
    // the current HTTP request, including the authenticated user's identity.
    //
    // ⚠️ IMPORTANT: HttpContext is ONLY available in static server-side
    // rendering (SSR) mode — the default when no @rendermode directive is set.
    // If you later add @rendermode InteractiveServer to this page (e.g., to
    // make buttons interactive), HttpContext will be NULL and this page will
    // crash. For interactive pages, use AuthenticationStateProvider instead.
    [CascadingParameter]
    private HttpContext context { get; set; } = default!;
}

    private string UserName = "User";
    private List<string> UserRoles = new();
    private decimal TotalRevenue;
    private int SystemSoldUnits;
    private int ShrinkageCount;
    private int TotalUnitsSold => SystemSoldUnits + Math.Abs(ShrinkageCount);

    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        var authState = await AuthStateProvider.GetAuthenticationStateAsync();
        var user = authState.User;

        if (user.Identity?.IsAuthenticated == true)
        {
            UserName = user.Identity.Name ?? "User";
            foreach (var role in AppRoles.AllRoles)
            {
                if (user.IsInRole(role))
                    UserRoles.Add(role);
            }
        }

        using var context = await DbFactory.CreateDbContextAsync();
        var today = DateTime.UtcNow.Date;

        var salesToday = await context.Sales
            .Where(s => s.SaleDate >= today)
            .ToListAsync();

        TotalRevenue = salesToday
            .Where(s => !s.IsManualAdjustment)
            .Sum(s => s.QuantitySold * s.UnitPriceAtSale);

        SystemSoldUnits = salesToday
            .Where(s => !s.IsManualAdjustment)
            .Sum(s => s.QuantitySold);

        ShrinkageCount = salesToday
            .Where(s => s.IsManualAdjustment)
            .Sum(s => s.QuantitySold);
    }
}
</string></ApplicationDbContext>

